<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870403-0115 </DOCNO><HL> World Air Sale and Leaseback</HL><DD> 04/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WOAAIRLINES (AIR)AEROSPACE (ARO) </IN><DATELINE> OAKLAND, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   World Airways said it completed the previously announced $149 million sale and leaseback of four DC-10-30 aircraft.    The carrier said the transaction would help it take advantage of high aircraft values and low interest rates. The transaction also will help fund the retirement of $92.2 million of long-term debt and the retirement of 10 million preferred shares and warrants to buy one million common shares, and provide additional cash for working capital. </TEXT></DOC>